Symmetry can be understood in the context of periodical translational order, where objects are separated by fixed distances, in a given direction. The Bravais lattices are defined by type, number and direction of the allowable translations defining the symmetry space group (i.e. in a square lattice, objects can have a neighbour above, below, to the left or to the right, yielding four-fold symmetric allowable translations). Similar to the description of entropic order, the coordination number or number of nearest neighbours, ℓ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
